Derive f(x)=x^2 and evaluate slope at x=3

func1 <- expression(x^2)
my_deriv <- D(func1, "x")
my_deriv
## 2 * x
x <- 3
eval(my_deriv)
## [1] 6

Now derive P(a)=2(3a+2)^45 and find slope at a=1.2

func2 <- expression(2*(3*a+2)^4 - 5)
my_deriv2 <- D(func2, "a")
a <- 1.2
eval(my_deriv2)
## [1] 4214.784

Same thing with g(t)

func3 <- expression((-4*t)/((t^2 +1)^3))
my_deriv3 <- D(func3 , "t")
t <- 0
eval(func3)
## [1] 0
